The paper deals with adaptive sequential decision making, which is a central challenge in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses active learning, robotics, sequential experimental design, and active detection, which are all subfields of AI and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses optimization problems, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.RO (Robotics).
